  "notes": "Chilean Spanish. Moderate coda aspiration. /x/ → [x] with [ç] allophone before front vowels (gente [ˈçente]) — distinctive Chilean feature. Deaffrication [tʃ] → [ʃ] in casual speech (stigmatised). -d deletion common. Distinctive intonation.",
